Local development
-----------------
npm run dev          # http://localhost:3000
npm run build        # production build
npm run lint


Automated deploy (recommended)
------------------------------
One command does build -> push (ECR) -> upload compose/Caddyfile -> pull + restart on EC2:

./deploy/deploy.sh                               # deploy the current committed git SHA
./deploy/deploy.sh --no-build --tag <old-sha>    # roll back to a previous build
./deploy/deploy.sh --help                        # all options

deploy/ itself is local-only tooling (gitignored, not part of this repo) — it
isn't present in a fresh clone. Recreate deploy.sh / deploy.env there, pointing
deploy.env at your own server + ECR details, to deploy from a new machine.

The manual steps below are the same flow, broken out for reference / one-offs.


Build & push image to ECR (from this directory)
------------------------------------------------
ECR=<your-account-id>.dkr.ecr.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/my-website
TAG=$(git rev-parse --short HEAD)        # immutable, rollback-able tag

docker build -t $ECR:$TAG -t $ECR:latest .

aws ecr get-login-password --region us-east-1 | \
  docker login --username AWS --password-stdin $ECR

docker push $ECR:$TAG
docker push $ECR:latest

# (One-time) Enable ECR scan-on-push so every pushed image is scanned for CVEs:
#   aws ecr put-image-scanning-configuration --repository-name my-website \
#     --image-scanning-configuration scanOnPush=true --region us-east-1


Deploy on the server (EC2)
--------------------------
# NOTE: this repo is public — the real EC2 host and SSH key path are intentionally
# omitted here. Keep them in a local, untracked note (e.g. ~/.config/veridical-deploy).
ssh -i ~/.ssh/<your-key>.pem ec2-user@<your-ec2-host>

aws ecr get-login-password --region us-east-1 | \
  docker login --username AWS --password-stdin \
  <your-account-id>.dkr.ecr.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/my-website

# Deploy a specific build (recommended). Recreates only the app service; Caddy keeps running.
IMAGE_TAG=<git-sha> docker compose pull
IMAGE_TAG=<git-sha> docker compose up -d


Rollback
--------
# Re-deploy the previous known-good SHA:
IMAGE_TAG=<previous-git-sha> docker compose up -d


Stop everything
---------------
docker compose down
